Q.2 Case study on cyber security risk management Explain the control architecture and supporting processes??  [15M]
Definition:
•	Cybersecurity Risk Management identifies, assesses, and mitigates risks to protect fintech systems and customer data.
Case Study Example – Digital Bank:
•	A digital bank wants to protect its online and mobile banking applications from cyber threats like phishing, malware, and data breaches.
Control Architecture [5M]
1.	Perimeter Security: Firewalls, VPNs, and intrusion detection systems (IDS).
2.	Application Security: Secure coding practices, vulnerability scanning, and penetration testing.
3.	Data Security: Encryption for data at rest and in transit, tokenization of sensitive data.
4.	Access Control: Role-based access, multi-factor authentication, and identity management.
5.	Monitoring & Logging: Real-time monitoring, SIEM (Security Information and Event Management) for threat detection.
Supporting Processes [5M]
1.	Risk Assessment: Identify potential cyber threats and vulnerabilities.
2.	Incident Response: Procedures to handle breaches and mitigate damage.
3.	Compliance & Auditing: Ensure adherence to PCI DSS, RBI PSS, PSD2, and local regulations.
4.	Employee Awareness & Training: Educate staff about phishing, malware, and secure practices.
5.	Continuous Improvement: Regular review and update of policies, tools, and security controls.
Outcome:
•	Reduced risk of cyber attacks, fraud, and data breaches.
•	Ensured regulatory compliance and customer trust.

